Submitted By:            Combined: Douglas R. Reno (build fix) + still image + tune fix + TD OBU fix + clap fix
Date:                    2026-03-22
Initial Package Version: 1.21.2
Upstream Status:         Pending
Origin:                  Upstream (PR #1680) + four additional fixes
Description:             Fixes building libheif with SVT-AV1 4.0 and later.
                         Four changes on top of the original build fix:

                         1. Still image mode (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            avif=true, intra_period_length=-1, fps=1/1.

                         2. tune=SSIM fallback to PSNR (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            SVT-AV1 4.x requires CRF for tune=SSIM but libheif uses
                            CQP. Fall back silently to PSNR.

                         3. Strip Temporal Delimiter OBU from output bitstream:
                            AVIF spec (ISO 23000-22 §2.1) forbids TD OBUs in image
                            items. SVT-AV1 in avif mode prepends one (2 bytes).
                            Firefox rejects such files. Strip after encode.

                         4. Round DOWN odd dimensions in svt_query_encoded_size:
                            Rounding up (461->462) causes libheif to add a clap box
                            with offset=-(1/2) pixel — Firefox rejects per AVIF spec.
                            Rounding down (461->460): encoded<=input, libheif skips
                            clap box entirely. One pixel lost on odd-sized images,
                            imperceptible in practice.

--- libheif-1.21.2.orig/libheif/plugins/encoder_svt.cc	2026-03-21 20:55:59.000000000 +0000
+++ libheif-1.21.2/libheif/plugins/encoder_svt.cc	2026-03-22 15:34:40.009724983 +0000
@@ -666,11 +666,16 @@ void svt_query_encoded_size(void* encode
 
   // SVT-AV1 (as of version 1.2.1) can only create image sizes matching the chroma format. Add padding if necessary.
 
+  // Round DOWN for odd dimensions instead of up.
+  // Rounding up (input+1) causes libheif to add a clap box with offset=-(1/2)
+  // pixel — a non-integer offset that Firefox rejects per AVIF spec ISO 23000-22.
+  // Rounding down means encoded<=input: libheif skips the clap box entirely.
+  // The single lost pixel on odd-sized images is imperceptible.
   if (input_width < 64) {
     *encoded_width = 64;
   }
   else if (encoder->chroma == heif_chroma_420 && (input_width & 1) == 1) {
-    *encoded_width = input_width + 1;
+    *encoded_width = input_width - 1;
   }
   else {
     *encoded_width = input_width;
@@ -680,7 +685,7 @@ void svt_query_encoded_size(void* encode
     *encoded_height = 64;
   }
   else if (encoder->chroma != heif_chroma_444 && (input_height & 1) == 1) {
-    *encoded_height = input_height + 1;
+    *encoded_height = input_height - 1;
   }
   else {
     *encoded_height = input_height;
@@ -829,8 +834,15 @@ static heif_error svt_start_sequence_enc
   svt_config.tile_columns = int_log2(encoder->tile_cols);
 
 #if SVT_AV1_CHECK_VERSION(0, 9, 1)
+#if SVT_AV1_CHECK_VERSION(4, 0, 0)
